> I have a custom made wheel mount that does connect to the front bumper, but
> most front wheel mounts are screwed into the metal skin with six (or more)
> metal screws.
>

Nope just two in the metal skin of the front, right under the vent air intake
grille, and two to the bumper.

>
> On your problem . . .
>
> 1)  could you get some sort of vice grip onto the spining nut??  If you can
> get a grip on it, then you might be able to remove the bolt/screw from the
> front.
>

Well yeah I could but I guess I have to remove the dashboard and everything. :-)

>
> I had the same condition; a loose nut just under the fresh air vent.  I 'J B
> Weld' the nut to the skin on the inside.
>

What's JB Weld?

>
> Actually, I 'J B Welded' the nut to a large fender washer while it was on my
> work bench.  The next day, when it was cured, I 'J B Welded' the  washer
> with attached nut to the skin.
>
> I was very careful NOT to get any of the 'J B Weld' in the threads of the
> nut or the threads of the bolt.
>

